.TH "mii_check_link" 9 "mii_check_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mii_check_link \- check MII link status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mii_check_link
.BI "(struct mii_if_info *mii "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mii" 12
MII interface
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the link status changed (previous != current), call
\fBnetif_carrier_on\fP if current link status is Up or call
\fBnetif_carrier_off\fP if current link status is Down.
